So
- as I said above - my views and hopes have changed.
It is
clear that for all practicable purposes the Communists are going to control
all of China.
Our only hope is to win them over to our side down
through
the years ahead.
I
believe the British Government and the U.S. too will
secord them some form of recognition and get along with them the best we
can.
Let's hope that being
Chinese their good sense will predominate and
that while
they may be 100% Russian-type today that tomorrow they may con-
promise in the old
Chinese way and take at least a middle of the road
course.
Bondy and I are very much on the spot because 80% of NAC is owned
by the Nationalist Government and we,
representing the minority interest,
have to go along with the majority unless our own Government instructs us
to do otherwise and agrees to stand the consequences.
So far we have had
little help
from any
quarter and I guess we'll have to work it out together
the best we
can with our sheped heads.
We may get instructions any day to move the whole fleet of 50
airplanes to Formosa or Hainan.
All we can do is try to hold on until the
so-called Nationel Government folds up snd
then try
the best we can to get
along with the new regime.
In the meantime attempt - to the extent that
we can - to preserve the assets of CNAC.
There's never a dull moment !
Bix
